realIQ.name: Cattell-Horn-Carroll model
realIQ.description: An online assessment based on the Cattell-Horn-Carroll model measuring fluid intelligence, working memory, and pattern recognition.
realIQ.testNotes: Resting state: After nap, good meal, and quiet environment. 13 minutes remaining on the test.

wais.name: Wechsler Adult Intelligence Scale (WAIS-IV)
wais.description: The WAIS is one of the most widely used intelligence tests for adults, measuring cognitive ability across different domains.
wais.conversionNotes: Estimated from RealIQ score using standard SD=15 conversion tables for high-range scores

stanfordBinet.name: Stanford-Binet Intelligence Scale
stanfordBinet.description: The Stanford-Binet test measures five factors of cognitive ability and provides a detailed analysis of intellectual capabilities.
stanfordBinet.conversionNotes: Estimated from RealIQ score using Stanford-Binet scale conversion (SD=16)

ravenProgressive.name: Raven's Progressive Matrices
ravenProgressive.description: A non-verbal test that measures abstract reasoning and fluid intelligence through pattern recognition.
ravenProgressive.conversionNotes: Estimated from RealIQ score; high score expected due to strong pattern recognition abilities

cattellCultureFair.name: Cattell Culture Fair Intelligence Test
cattellCultureFair.description: Designed to measure fluid intelligence while minimizing cultural and educational biases.
cattellCultureFair.conversionNotes: Estimated from RealIQ results with SD=24 scale; closely related to the RealIQ test model

workingMemory.name: N-Back Working Memory Assessment
workingMemory.description: Measures working memory capacity, attention control, and fluid intelligence.
workingMemory.conversionNotes: Estimated from RealIQ score; blog post indicates high working memory abilities

processingSpeed.name: Cognitive Processing Speed Index
processingSpeed.description: Measures the speed of mental processing and visual-motor coordination.
processingSpeed.conversionNotes: Estimated from RealIQ score; blog post mentions processing speed as a component of intelligence tests
